* ML Environments
** Databricks Runtime ML
***_ Pre-installed ML libraries
***_ GPU drivers + CUDA
***_ TensorFlow, PyTorch, etc.
***_ Reduces setup time
** Hardware for ML
*** Single-node for experimentation
****_ Minimal shuffle overhead
****_ Good starting point
*** GPU instances for deep learning
****_ Image recognition, NLP, neural nets
****_ 10-100x faster than CPU
****_ Disable Photon when using GPU
** Typical ML workflow
***_ Start single-node for experiments
***_ Scale to GPU for model training
***_ Use Databricks Runtime ML always
@endmindmap
